    <subsubsection>
      <title><xref ref="exer_find_ds"></xref> Select Answers and Hints</title>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <p>
            The graph is drawn in <xref ref="fig_complete_graphs_12345"></xref>.
            The degree sequence is <m>4,4,4,4,4</m>.
            It is regular.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Hint: Your drawing should have three black vertices,
            four white vertices, and every possible black-white edge.
            The degree sequence is <m>4,4,4,3,3,3,3</m>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Hint: The graph has a total of seven vertices and the degree sequence is <m>6,1,1,1,1,1,1</m>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Hint: The graph has a total of six vertices and five edges.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Hint: The graph is 2-regular and has five vertices.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Hint: The graph has a total of seven vertices and the degree sequence is <m>6,3,3,3,3,3,3</m>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Hint: The graph should look <xref ref="fig_L2x4">like</xref>
            but without <m>v_4</m> and <m>w_4</m> (and edges to them.)
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
